{
  "$schema": "agent-registry",
  "version": "1.1",
  "dual_phase_definition": "true = agent has a distinct PLAN phase followed by an EXECUTE phase (e.g., reads codebase, proposes approach, then implements). false = agent is single-phase execution: it receives a task and executes directly without an internal plan-then-act split. Agents without explicit internal planning (pure analysis, pure retrieval, pure review) are false.",
  "compatibility_schema": "v1: optional free-form string per agent declaring runtime preconditions (e.g., 'Requires monitor running at 127.0.0.1:16145 for HTML primary emission'). Absent/null/undefined → agent is always available (backwards-compatible default). Orchestrator Compatibility Probe checks this field pre-delegation and halts with remediation hint when preconditions are unmet. Frontmatter `compatibility:` on the agent .md is the per-agent canonical source; registry entries mirror it for routing-time lookup.",
  "phases": {
    "research": 1,
    "analysis": 2,
    "planning": 3,
    "implementation": 4,
    "review": 5,
    "report": 6
  },
